
PROGRAM HELLO  ! Declares the start of a Fortran program.

	PRINT *, 'Hello World!'  ! This print a mensage Wow!
	! (PRINT) -> instruction that displays something on the console.
	! (*) -> standard formatting
	! (Hello World) -> a string literal that will be printed
END PROGRAM HELLO ! (END PROGRAM <NAME>) -> Marks the end of the program.

